freenet.keys
Class ClientCHK

java.lang.Object
  freenet.keys.BaseClientKey
      freenet.keys.ClientKey
          freenet.keys.ClientCHK

public class ClientCHK
extends ClientKey

Client level CHK. Can be converted into a FreenetURI, can be used to decrypt a CHKBlock, can be produced by a CHKBlock.

ClientCHK

public ClientCHK(byte[] routingKey,
                 byte[] encKey,
                 boolean isControlDocument,
                 byte algo,
                 short compressionAlgorithm)
Parameters:
routingKey - The routing key. This is the overall hash of the header and content of the key.
encKey - The decryption key. This is not passed to other nodes and is extracted from the URI.
isCompressed - True if the data was gzipped before encoding.
isControlDocument - True if the document is a Control Document. These carry metadata, whereas ordinary keys carry data, and have no type.
algo - The encryption algorithm's identifier. See ALGO_* for values.
